<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-02-06T13:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-02-06T13:36:00-05:00" n="282" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">412.00/116: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-02-06T12:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">February 6,
                                        1920—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 11:40
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>28. Department’s mail instruction number 1161 October 9, 1919.</p>
                        <p>The Acting Minister for Foreign Affairs called me to the Foreign Office
                            last evening to say that the Mexican Government is now prepared to enter
                            into an arrangement for the consideration by a mixed commission of
                            American claims against Mexico and Mexican claims against the United
                            States.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>